\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Phase-Locked Molecular Ensembles as Reality Compression.} \textbf  {(Top)} Individual O$_2$ molecules (gray spheres) with independent phases $\phi _i$ (arrows). Without phase-locking, tracking requires $N \times \log _2 M$ bits for $N$ molecules in $M$ states. \textbf  {(Middle)} Van der Waals and paramagnetic coupling (blue and red bonds) synchronize molecular oscillations within coherence length $\xi _{\text  {coh}} \approx 14$ nm, creating phase-locked ensemble of ~$10^4$ molecules. All phases satisfy $|\phi _i - \phi _j| < \pi /4$ (yellow highlighted region). \textbf  {(Bottom)} Ensemble representation: Single collective phase $\phi _{\text  {ensemble}}$, size $N_{\text  {ens}}$, and coherence quality $\Delta \phi $ encode entire ensemble state in ~15 bits, achieving $\sim 10^4$× compression. Phase structure (waveform) encodes complete environmental state: temperature (coherence lifetime $\tau _{\text  {coh}}$), pressure (ensemble density), chemistry (paramagnetic spectrum), and dynamics (phase drift, decay rate). This compression makes brain processing of 10$^{22}$ molecules/breath computationally tractable via $\sim 10^7$ ensembles - 10$^{15}$× reduction critical for singularity viability.}}{12}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:phase_lock}{{2}{12}{\textbf {Phase-Locked Molecular Ensembles as Reality Compression.} \textbf {(Top)} Individual O$_2$ molecules (gray spheres) with independent phases $\phi _i$ (arrows). Without phase-locking, tracking requires $N \times \log _2 M$ bits for $N$ molecules in $M$ states. \textbf {(Middle)} Van der Waals and paramagnetic coupling (blue and red bonds) synchronize molecular oscillations within coherence length $\xi _{\text {coh}} \approx 14$ nm, creating phase-locked ensemble of ~$10^4$ molecules. All phases satisfy $|\phi _i - \phi _j| < \pi /4$ (yellow highlighted region). \textbf {(Bottom)} Ensemble representation: Single collective phase $\phi _{\text {ensemble}}$, size $N_{\text {ens}}$, and coherence quality $\Delta \phi $ encode entire ensemble state in ~15 bits, achieving $\sim 10^4$× compression. Phase structure (waveform) encodes complete environmental state: temperature (coherence lifetime $\tau _{\text {coh}}$), pressure (ensemble density), chemistry (paramagnetic spectrum), and dynamics (phase drift, decay rate). This compression makes brain processing of 10$^{22}$ molecules/breath computationally tractable via $\sim 10^7$ ensembles - 10$^{15}$× reduction critical for singularity viability}{figure.caption.3}{}}
