\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Vibrational Förster Resonance Energy Transfer (vFRET) Landscape.} \textbf  {(A)} Energy level diagram: O$_2$ vibrational states (red ladder, $\omega _{O_2} = 1580$ cm$^{-1}$) and lipid C-C stretch modes (blue ladder, $\omega _{\text  {lipid}} \approx 1000$ cm$^{-1}$). Resonance condition satisfied when $|\omega _{O_2} - \omega _{\text  {lipid}}| < 10\%$ (green overlap region). Transfer pathway: $|O_2: \nu +1\rangle |\text  {lipid}: n\rangle \rightarrow |O_2: \nu \rangle |\text  {lipid}: n+1\rangle $. \textbf  {(B)} Coupling strength vs separation: Van der Waals dipole-dipole interaction $V_{\text  {coupling}} \propto r^{-3}$ (purple curve). At optimal distance $r \approx 0.3$ nm (membrane-O$_2$ interface), $V_{\text  {coupling}} \approx 10$ meV. Gray shaded region shows effective coupling range (0.2-0.5 nm). \textbf  {(C)} Transfer rate Fermi's golden rule: $k_{\text  {vFRET}} = (2\pi /\hbar ) |V_{\text  {coupling}}|^2 \rho (\omega )$ yields $k \approx 10^{12}$ s$^{-1}$ (1 ps transfer time). Heatmap shows rate dependence on $V$ and density of states $\rho $. White contour marks physiological regime. \textbf  {(D)} Categorical encoding mechanism: Different categorical states $C_i$ (orange), $C_j$ (cyan), $C_k$ (magenta) produce different vibrational population distributions $\{a_\nu (C)\}$. Each distribution creates unique transfer pattern (spectral fingerprint) detectable by membrane. \textbf  {(E)} Transfer efficiency vs temperature: Room temperature (300 K, red star) provides optimal thermal population spread across $\nu = 0$-3. Too cold (blue): all molecules in $\nu =0$ (no information diversity). Too hot (red): excessive thermal broadening. Evolution tuned biological temperature for maximum information transfer. \textbf  {(F)} Membrane lipid response: Transmitted energy creates oscillatory holes at original O$_2$ frequency (yellow gaps in blue spectrum) - P-type information (absence) complementing N-type (molecular presence). This vFRET process is core physical mechanism enabling O$_2$ categorical information to transfer to membrane.}}{32}{figure.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:vibrational_landscape}{{5}{32}{\textbf {Vibrational Förster Resonance Energy Transfer (vFRET) Landscape.} \textbf {(A)} Energy level diagram: O$_2$ vibrational states (red ladder, $\omega _{O_2} = 1580$ cm$^{-1}$) and lipid C-C stretch modes (blue ladder, $\omega _{\text {lipid}} \approx 1000$ cm$^{-1}$). Resonance condition satisfied when $|\omega _{O_2} - \omega _{\text {lipid}}| < 10\%$ (green overlap region). Transfer pathway: $|O_2: \nu +1\rangle |\text {lipid}: n\rangle \rightarrow |O_2: \nu \rangle |\text {lipid}: n+1\rangle $. \textbf {(B)} Coupling strength vs separation: Van der Waals dipole-dipole interaction $V_{\text {coupling}} \propto r^{-3}$ (purple curve). At optimal distance $r \approx 0.3$ nm (membrane-O$_2$ interface), $V_{\text {coupling}} \approx 10$ meV. Gray shaded region shows effective coupling range (0.2-0.5 nm). \textbf {(C)} Transfer rate Fermi's golden rule: $k_{\text {vFRET}} = (2\pi /\hbar ) |V_{\text {coupling}}|^2 \rho (\omega )$ yields $k \approx 10^{12}$ s$^{-1}$ (1 ps transfer time). Heatmap shows rate dependence on $V$ and density of states $\rho $. White contour marks physiological regime. \textbf {(D)} Categorical encoding mechanism: Different categorical states $C_i$ (orange), $C_j$ (cyan), $C_k$ (magenta) produce different vibrational population distributions $\{a_\nu (C)\}$. Each distribution creates unique transfer pattern (spectral fingerprint) detectable by membrane. \textbf {(E)} Transfer efficiency vs temperature: Room temperature (300 K, red star) provides optimal thermal population spread across $\nu = 0$-3. Too cold (blue): all molecules in $\nu =0$ (no information diversity). Too hot (red): excessive thermal broadening. Evolution tuned biological temperature for maximum information transfer. \textbf {(F)} Membrane lipid response: Transmitted energy creates oscillatory holes at original O$_2$ frequency (yellow gaps in blue spectrum) - P-type information (absence) complementing N-type (molecular presence). This vFRET process is core physical mechanism enabling O$_2$ categorical information to transfer to membrane}{figure.caption.7}{}}
